author: Tim Rostan
title: Army parachutist dies of injuries sustained Saturday in Chicago show: report
text: One of the two parachutists involved in a midair collision Saturday during the Chicago Air and Water Show has died of his injuries , the Chicago Sun-Times is reporting. Sgt. First Class Corey Hood, a member of the Army Golden Knights team, died at about 4 p.m. Sunday, the Cook County medical examiner's office reported, the Sun-Times said. The second parachutist is a Navy Leap Frogs member who sustained a leg injury in a hard landing on North Avenue Beach. The Golden Knights parachutist landed unconscious at the base of an apartment building across Lake Shore Drive, having reportedly struck a terrace more than 20 stories above, according to a WLS-TV report.
